description:
Stardew Valley is an open-ended country-life RPG. You can farm, fish, mine, fight, complete quests,
befriend villagers, and uncover dark secrets.

0.5.1-stardew-6.8.2-tracker.description:
# Changelog (only when Universal Tracker is installed)
- Universal Tracker patch from the previous release 
- Add a Stardew Valley Tracker client in the Archipelago Launcher
  - Add `/explain` `/explain_item` `/explain_how` `/explain_missing` and `/more` commands that explain the logic rules behind a location or an item.

# Known issues
- Sometime, the logic for a location is so large it will crash the client. It happens noticeably with bundles and community center room locations.
- If the client starts lagging, restart it. 
- The link will not appear in AP Launcher if UT is not installed in the custom_worlds.
- Icon is broken... (fixed in AP 0.6.0)
- Clicking on the suggestion when making a typo will autofill a `!hint` command instead of the `/explain` command.

# Compatibility tested with
- [Stardew Valley Archipelago 6.x.x](https://github.com/agilbert1412/StardewArchipelago/releases) 
- [Archipelago 0.5.1](https://github.com/ArchipelagoMW/Archipelago/releases) 
- [Universal Tracker v0.1.15.1](https://github.com/FarisTheAncient/Archipelago/releases) 

# Installation instruction (for windows)
- Place the new `stardew_valley.apworld` in your custom world folder
- Remove the old `stardew_valley.apworld` from your lib/worlds folder
0.5.1-stardew-6.8.2-tracker.title: Stardew Valley Tracker Beta 2 (Archipelago 0.5.1)

7.2.7.description:
## Apworld

- Improved the item link test

- Fixed an issue where shops could hint their content even if they didn't scout it
- Fixed an issue where buildings ER could place the farmhouse in a door that is inaccessible based on "Start Without"
- Changed the Scout-hinting config to allow more granular control over which items are hinted. Default is scout nothing in solo, and only progression items in multiworlds
7.2.7.title: StardewArchipelago Release 7.2.7

7.2.8.description:

- Fixed a bug where some scout operations could crash when only some of the locations didn't exist
7.2.8.title: StardewArchipelago Release 7.2.8

7.2.9.description:
## Apworld
- Fixed error with TotalReceived handling str
- Improved formatting for some forced options messages
- Fixed an issue with the raccoon shop not getting all the items at once
- Added apworld manifest to comply with AP 0.7.0
- Fixed traveling merchant rules being applied twice
- Added "not winter" rule to Vista
- Corrected typo in my name
- Fixed some early candidates not making sense depending on Start Without
- Fixes to logic loops in some Fish Pond fishes

## Mod
- Disable throwing items in water if you don't have the related meme bundles (it will also disable once the bundles are done)
- Added a bunch of try catch for more info in error messages during parsing of internal data like recipes
7.2.9.title: StardewArchipelago Release 7.2.9

7.3.0.description:
## Apworld
- Disallow Ultimate Foodie goal with only poisonous foods, because the way it works is Poisonous adds itself to other settings, so that made for an empty goal (thanks @palex00)
- Fixed Determinism in Catch and Release Bundle
- Removed pointless sharding log

## Mod
- Updated to ArchipelagoUtilities 3.1.0
  - Custom Assets are no longer packaged with the mod (file size went down a bit). They are instead downloaded on-demand when encountering items from other games. They are kept in `%AppData%\Local\ArchipelagoUtilities\Custom Assets`, and downloaded assets will be usable by all games that use the custom assets system, without needing to duplicate the files a bunch of times. Players can also add assets there to use in all their games.
  - Stardew will re-download the assets after 28 days of inactivity, or if the local storage is cleared.
  - ArchipelagoUtilities and AssetDownloader are now two libraries, allowing others to only reference the assets without the rest of the utilities
  - Some Interfaces are in a separate assembly for cleanliness
- Updated to MultiClient 6.7.0
- Save Scout hints in the save file, preventing them from being scout-hinted again later
7.3.0.title: StardewArchipelago Release 7.3.0

7.3.1.description:
- Added a few more null checks while scouting
- Don't initialize custom assets at all if the player turned them off from the config
- Fixed an issue where the assets folder would not get created the first time
7.3.1.title: StardewArchipelago Release 7.3.1

7.3.10.description:
## Apworld
- Made some tests faster and simpler
- Use string keys in slot data because some json libraries are more strict about int keys (Fixes [Issue #5825](https://github.com/ArchipelagoMW/Archipelago/issues/5825))
- Added Fragments of the past completion rule to Geode Order. This has no effect on actual logic, because Geode Order already had strictly higher requirements, but it will make it so explaining tools like UT will show this, and help the player figure out that they need to complete Fragments of the Past.

## Mod
### Ported from 6.11.9
- Fixed an issue with special orders not triggering mail flags, which could mess with other special orders when they had a dependency on said mail flag
- Added a Reroll button to special orders. Can be used as much as you want. Intended to make it easier to find specific special orders you might want to do this week.
- Reduced chance of preferential pick on special orders from 75% to 25%, due to the reroll button making preferential rolls significantly less valuable
7.3.10.title: StardewArchipelago Release 7.3.10

7.3.11.description:
## Apworld
- Fixed an issue where shorter special order settings would accidentally not trigger some location rules
- Made the Qi's cuisine logic rule a bit more forgiving, for players using seed shop overhaul
- Added Topology Present

## Mod

7.3.2.description:
## Apworld
- Added alias "all" to Shipsanity: Everything

## Mod
- Added a warning for supported mods of the wrong version, at boot time, so people don't need to connect to a multiworld to check their versions. This warning can be ignored, as the player might not intend to connect to a modded slot anyway.
- Ported changes from [6.11.6](https://github.com/agilbert1412/StardewArchipelago/releases/tag/6.11.6)
- Jojapocalypse
  - Added Endgame locations Consequences
  - Added Hatsanity Consequences
  - Added Eatsanity Consequences
  - Added two new config settings. They don't do anything when not playing Jojapocalypse
    -  `JojapocalypseHarderGoals`: Makes some of the goals that rely on locations only, have a few extra related conditions when you are a Joja member, to make them harder to cheese through Joja. Defaults
    - `JojapocalypseMinimumCompletionPercentToGoal`: Optional threshold of checks that must be reached before a Joja member can goal. Defaults to 50, meaning you must do at least half your slot before goaling. Can go from 0-100
  - Fixed several bugs related to the Movie Theater unlock when you are a Joja Member
  - Added some price variance to the Joja stock so not everything costs the same
  - Updated local ID Tables
  - Allow Perfection Waivers for Jojapocalypse Slots
  - Introduced dynamic grouping of Jojapocalypse checks, using keywords, to make the menus significantly easier to navigate
  - Added Small Pack filters

7.3.6.description:
- Nerfed Eatsanity consequences
- Changed the math behind inflation traps to introduce a progressive softcapping system leading to less out-of-control growth for prices of basic materials, but they can still get quite expensive. In short, the multiplier on prices gets softcapped on every order of magnitude (power of 10), using the nth root of the value over the threshold. So up to x10 it's unchanged, then between x10 and x100, you get (10 + SquareRoot(val-10)), then between x100 and x1000 you get (100 + CubeRoot(val-100)), and so on. Every inflation trap therefore still increases prices, but significantly less harshly, the higher it already is.
- Fixed several Joja shop prices which were strange due to inconsistent internal data values.
- Removed some undesired items from the joja shop stock (walnuts, stardrops, etc)
7.3.6.title: StardewArchipelago Release 7.3.6

7.3.7.description:
## Apworld
- Fixed start inventory items not being considered during UT generation, which could desync the entire seeded random events like ER

## Mod
- Fixed Joja shop ~~harassment~~ advertisements not working for locations with `#` in the name [BeagleGaming1]
- Fixed Clint's shop not "benefitting" from inflation traps (apparently this has been broken since SV 1.6...)

7.3.8.description:

7.3.8.title: StardewArchipelago Release 7.3.8

7.3.9.description:
- Updated ArchipelagoUtilities, Multiclient.net, and Gifting
- Fixed some Jojapocalypse checks getting filtered on the wrong recipe names and not showing up in the shop
- Moved the traveling cart Tea Set to Year 10, from year 25
- Fixed the number of crafting recipes to omit from Craft master goal when ginger island is excluded (ported fix from 6.x.x)
- Added new config: RemoteCommunityCenter (default: true). When this is turned on, Bundles will automatically completed themselves locally when the mod detects that they were completed on the server (from `/send_location`, `!collect`, and slot cooping). This also happens when you have a joja membership, since the actual bundle becomes unreachable
7.3.9.title: StardewArchipelago Release 7.3.9

7.4.0r3.description:
# This is a breaking update from 7.3.0 due to renaming some locations

## Apworld
- New Setting: CustomLogic
  - Allows you to toggle various flags to customize the logic of the world generator on many fronts. Most make the logic looser (and, as a result, expect more from the player -> harder difficulty), but some make it stricter (expect less from the player -> easier difficulty)
  - Some flags are inherently incompatible. When choosing multiple, the hardest flag takes priority. So if you enable "Extreme Fishing" **and** "Hard Fishing", only Extreme fishing will apply.
  - Some looser logic rules can lead to having to reset days in some cases. For example, "Critical Free Samples" expects that you will use your free sample of seeds to do the related checks, instead of garanteeing renewable access. You could lose the seed pack to a monster and have to reset the day.
  - Gameplay in the mod not actually affected. Only logic in the generator is.
  - Open to suggestions for more CustomLogic toggles!
- Added prefixes to all secretsanity locations
- Added prefixes to Desert Chef meal locations
- Reworked the Desert Chef. Now, on easy, you need to eat one any food. On hard, you need to eat 1 specific food. This will lead to less clutter.
- Added options missing in option groups
- Allow UT to read some settings from slot data (the ones that are there), and automatically adapt to them. This means that it will be a bit more forgiving to most yaml errors, but you still need a yaml, because not everything actually is in slot data. About 80% of options are now self-correcting in this way
- Fixed Roe accidentally requiring a fish smoker instead of a fish pond (how did this go unnoticed so long lmao)
- Update to the setup guides, to mention some of the more recent Archipelago website features such as "Generate Single Player Game" and presets. It was pretty outdated.

## Mod
- Ported the Master Angler fix from [6.11.10](https://github.com/agilbert1412/StardewArchipelago/releases/tag/6.11.10)
- Implemented Archipelago Textures at the Lupini paintings (optional, config defaults to ON). This can use CustomAssets or generic classification assets, based on your other configs. This should reduce time wasted, waiting for 5pm to buy a Lupini, if you can visually see that it will be useless.
- Updated AssetDownloader. It had issues displaying assets for items with `<` in the name, such as stardew hearts.
- Changed Multisleep Behavior config's default value, from `Repeat` to `Prompt`, to help new players not accidentally miss the season prompt.
7.4.0r3.title: StardewArchipelago Release 7.4.0

7.4.1.description:
- If Tools are not shuffled, ignore the Start Without Tools toggle
- Remember JotPK furthest progress so far
- When loading a JotPK save, on shuffled arcade machines, apply new upgrades that were received in-between
- When starting a new JotPK Journey, allow the player to pick the starting world, from the worlds they have reached at least once.
